
[1]ceruse

   CERUSE, n. White-lead; a carbonate of lead, produced by exposing the
   metal in thin plates to the vapor of vinegar. Lead is sometimes found
   native in the form of ceruse.

   Ceruse of antimony is a white oxyd of antimony, which separates from
   the water in which diaphoretic antimony has been washed.
